stanford pan asian music festival elegant gathering iii arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe calendar stanford pan asian music festival elegant gathering iii saturday february 11 2012 1 00pm dinkelspiel auditorium free lectures and demonstrations associated with the eighth annual pan asian music festival take the format of elegant gatherings an ancient term used to describe a gathering of scholars and artists anna schultz ethnomusicology professor in the department of music moderates a panel discussion with the theme from the silk road to today's world of music that will explore the past and the continuing transformation of asian music followed by a chinese tea ceremony performed by tea master chiung chih lin presented in collaboration with the center for east asian studies at stanford sponsored by department of music home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
